{
  "format": "tiptap/v1",
  "doc": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Cross-charge reconciliation is the process of verifying that what was charged to each consumer team matches what those teams actually consumed \u2014 and that the internal rate applied was the correct one in force at the time. When discrepancies exist, the dispute process provides a structured path to resolution that maintains trust between the platform team and consumer teams without turning every billing cycle into a contested exercise."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Cross-charge reconciliation and dispute process",
          "title": "Monthly reconciliation cycle and dispute resolution path"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The monthly reconciliation cycle"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Reconciliation begins when the provider invoice arrives and ends when each consumer team has received and acknowledged their chargeback invoice. The cycle typically runs on a 5\u201310 business day cadence after the provider's billing close date."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Provider invoice arrives (typically on the 1st\u20135th of the month for the prior month's usage)."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "FinOps team imports the invoice line items into the usage ledger and matches them to internally tracked usage records by model ID and billing period."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Per-team usage aggregates are computed from the usage ledger, grouped by model ID."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "The rate card version in effect during the billing period is applied to each team's usage to compute their internal chargeback amount."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Chargeback invoices are generated for each team and sent with the supporting usage detail report."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "A 10-business-day dispute window opens from the date of invoice delivery."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Disputes are resolved and credit notes issued within 15 business days of the original invoice date."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Reconciliation data model"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The reconciliation data model must be able to reproduce any invoice from first principles: given a team ID, a billing period, and a rate card version, it must be possible to re-derive the exact charge. This audit capability is essential for dispute resolution and for external audits."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from dataclasses import dataclass, field\nfrom typing import List, Optional\nimport datetime\n\n@dataclass\nclass UsageLedgerEntry:\n    \"\"\"One model call's usage record as logged by the AI gateway.\"\"\"\n    entry_id: str\n    team_id: str\n    model_id: str\n    timestamp_utc: str\n    input_tokens: int\n    output_tokens: int\n    cache_read_tokens: int\n    request_id: str\n    conversation_id: Optional[str] = None\n\n@dataclass\nclass ChargebackLineItem:\n    model_id: str\n    total_input_tokens: int\n    total_output_tokens: int\n    total_cache_tokens: int\n    rate_card_version: str\n    input_rate_per_1m: float\n    output_rate_per_1m: float\n    cache_rate_per_1m: float\n\n    @property\n    def amount_usd(self) -> float:\n        return (self.total_input_tokens / 1e6 * self.input_rate_per_1m\n                + self.total_output_tokens / 1e6 * self.output_rate_per_1m\n                + self.total_cache_tokens / 1e6 * self.cache_rate_per_1m)\n\n@dataclass\nclass ChargebackInvoice:\n    invoice_id: str\n    team_id: str\n    period: str            # \"2026-07\"\n    issued_date: str       # ISO date\n    line_items: List[ChargebackLineItem] = field(default_factory=list)\n    credit_notes: List[float] = field(default_factory=list)\n\n    @property\n    def subtotal_usd(self) -> float:\n        return sum(li.amount_usd for li in self.line_items)\n\n    @property\n    def total_usd(self) -> float:\n        return self.subtotal_usd - sum(self.credit_notes)\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Handling shared API keys and split attribution"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "In some organisations, multiple teams share a single API key for a particular model or workflow. Shared keys make attribution more difficult because the provider reports usage at the key level, not the team level. When shared keys are unavoidable, split attribution rules must be defined in advance and documented in the rate card governance record."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Define the split rule before usage begins: proportional split by conversation count, equal split, or fixed-weight split agreed by the sharing teams."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Instrument the shared key with request-level metadata: even on a shared key, each API call can carry a team_id or workflow_id header that the gateway logs for attribution."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Treat shared keys as a temporary measure: every shared key should have a sunset date and a plan to migrate to per-team keys. Shared keys with no sunset plan accumulate attribution debt that becomes unresolvable."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Disclose split attribution rules to finance: during reconciliation, flag line items derived from shared-key splits rather than direct attribution so auditors can evaluate the methodology."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Cross-fiscal-year reconciliation"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Provider invoices that arrive in January for December usage create a cross-fiscal-year reconciliation challenge. The cost belongs to the prior fiscal year for accrual accounting purposes, but the provider invoice arrives after the books are closed."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Accrue estimated December usage by December 31 based on the month-to-date actual spend and the expected remaining days. This ensures the P&L for the fiscal year reflects the full AI cost."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "When the January invoice arrives, reconcile the accrual against the actual: if the accrual was within 5% of the actual, no restatement is needed; larger variances require a true-up adjustment in the January books."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Document the accrual methodology so auditors can verify it \u2014 typically 'pro-rata based on daily average of the first 25 days of December'."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Set the dispute window for December invoices to 15 business days (instead of 10) to account for holiday periods where team leads are less available to review invoices."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Common reconciliation discrepancies"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Discrepancies between the provider invoice and the internal chargeback have a small set of common causes. Knowing the taxonomy speeds up investigation."
          }
        ]
      },
