      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Implementing the dispute process"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The dispute process must be fast, transparent, and self-documenting. Consumer teams need to be able to raise a dispute without needing to understand the internal ledger \u2014 they should only need to point to the line item they are challenging and state why."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from dataclasses import dataclass, field\nfrom enum import Enum\nfrom typing import Optional\nimport datetime\n\nclass DisputeStatus(Enum):\n    OPEN = \"open\"\n    UNDER_REVIEW = \"under_review\"\n    UPHELD = \"upheld\"       # charge corrected\n    REJECTED = \"rejected\"   # original charge confirmed\n    WITHDRAWN = \"withdrawn\" # team withdrew the dispute\n\nclass DisputeReason(Enum):\n    USAGE_NOT_MINE = \"usage_not_mine\"\n    DOUBLE_COUNTED = \"double_counted\"\n    WRONG_RATE = \"wrong_rate\"\n    CREDIT_NOT_APPLIED = \"credit_not_applied\"\n    DATA_ERROR = \"data_error\"\n    OTHER = \"other\"\n\n@dataclass\nclass ChargebackDispute:\n    dispute_id: str\n    invoice_id: str\n    team_id: str\n    disputed_amount_usd: float\n    reason: DisputeReason\n    description: str\n    submitted_at: str = field(default_factory=lambda: datetime.datetime.utcnow().isoformat())\n    status: DisputeStatus = DisputeStatus.OPEN\n    reviewer: Optional[str] = None\n    resolution_note: Optional[str] = None\n    credit_issued_usd: float = 0.0\n    resolved_at: Optional[str] = None\n\n    def resolve(\n        self,\n        upheld: bool,\n        reviewer: str,\n        note: str,\n        credit_usd: float = 0.0,\n    ) -> None:\n        self.status = DisputeStatus.UPHELD if upheld else DisputeStatus.REJECTED\n        self.reviewer = reviewer\n        self.resolution_note = note\n        self.credit_issued_usd = credit_usd\n        self.resolved_at = datetime.datetime.utcnow().isoformat()\n\n    @property\n    def days_open(self) -> int:\n        submitted = datetime.datetime.fromisoformat(self.submitted_at)\n        return (datetime.datetime.utcnow() - submitted).days\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Credit note issuance and invoice restatement"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When a dispute is upheld, the FinOps team issues a credit note against the original invoice. The credit note reduces the team's next chargeback invoice by the credited amount. An uphold that resolves a large discrepancy may require a restated invoice for the affected period to provide a clean audit trail."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Credit note contents: dispute ID, original invoice ID, description of the error corrected, credit amount, and the period to which the credit applies."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Application: credits are applied to the next month's invoice, not returned as a cash payment. This simplifies the accounting treatment for both teams."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Restatement threshold: if the credit exceeds 5% of the original invoice, issue a restated invoice alongside the credit note for audit clarity."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Downstream impact: if the original overcharge caused the team to file a budget exception, the credit should be noted in the exception record and the team's budget utilisation updated accordingly."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Preventing reconciliation discrepancies"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The highest-ROI investment in reconciliation is preventing discrepancies rather than resolving them. Most discrepancies stem from one of three systemic issues: API key governance failures, gateway logging gaps, or rate card version mishandling in billing code."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "API key governance: enforce that all AI API keys are provisioned through the platform team's key management system with mandatory team_id metadata. Disable and rotate any keys found without team attribution."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Gateway completeness: track the ratio of gateway-logged tokens to provider-billed tokens each month. A ratio below 98% indicates a logging gap that must be investigated."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Rate card version pinning: the billing code must record the rate card version ID alongside each computed charge and validate it against the invoice period before sending invoices."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Automated pre-reconciliation check: before sending chargeback invoices, run an automated check that compares the sum of all team charges to the provider invoice total. If they differ by more than 2%, halt the invoice run and alert the FinOps team."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "def pre_reconciliation_check(\n    team_charges: dict,           # team_id \u2192 computed charge\n    provider_invoice_total: float,\n    tolerance_pct: float = 2.0,\n) -> dict:\n    internal_total = sum(team_charges.values())\n    gap_usd = provider_invoice_total - internal_total\n    gap_pct = gap_usd / provider_invoice_total * 100 if provider_invoice_total else 0\n    passed = abs(gap_pct) <= tolerance_pct\n    return {\n        \"passed\": passed,\n        \"provider_total\": provider_invoice_total,\n        \"internal_total\": round(internal_total, 2),\n        \"gap_usd\": round(gap_usd, 2),\n        \"gap_pct\": round(gap_pct, 2),\n        \"action\": \"proceed\" if passed else \"HALT \u2014 investigate gap before issuing invoices\",\n    }\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Reconciliation reporting and governance"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The reconciliation process generates governance data that should be tracked over time. A high dispute rate or a large gap between provider invoice and internal charges indicates systemic issues that need to be addressed at the programme level."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "table",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "tableRow",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "tableHeader",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
