      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Review reconciliation metrics in the monthly FinOps review. A persistent dispute rate above 10% indicates a structural problem \u2014 typically in usage attribution or rate card version management \u2014 that needs engineering intervention, not just process improvement."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Common mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "No dispute window on chargeback invoices: teams that discover errors three months later when they cannot file a dispute will lose trust in the billing system entirely."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Resolving disputes informally via Slack: informal resolutions are undocumented, cannot be audited, and lead to inconsistent treatment across teams."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Not archiving credit notes: credit notes are financial documents; losing them creates audit gaps when reconciling year-end P&Ls."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Treating a 100% uphold rate as a sign of good disputes: a 100% uphold rate on submitted disputes usually means teams are only disputing clear errors \u2014 they may be absorbing incorrect charges for grey-area discrepancies that they cannot prove."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Key takeaways"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "The monthly reconciliation cycle runs from provider invoice receipt through chargeback invoice delivery and dispute resolution \u2014 a 15-business-day process."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "The reconciliation data model must be able to reproduce any invoice from first principles: team ID + period + rate card version \u2192 charge."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Run a pre-reconciliation gap check before sending any invoices \u2014 a gap above 2% warrants investigation before charges are issued."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Credit notes should be applied to the next invoice rather than paid in cash, and restated invoices should be issued for credits exceeding 5% of the original."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Track reconciliation governance metrics (dispute rate, uphold rate, gap) monthly and treat persistent anomalies as systemic engineering problems, not isolated billing errors."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
